com.vmware.vapi.metadata.cli

Interface Command

  • All Superinterfaces:
    CommandTypes, Service
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CommandStub

    public interface Command
extends Service, CommandTypes
    The Command interface provides methods to get information about command line interface (CLI) commands.

    • Method Detail

      • list

        java.util.List<CommandTypes.Identity> list(java.lang.String path)
        Returns the identifiers of all commands, or commands in a specific namespace.

        Synchronous method overload. Result of the invocation will be reported as a method return value.

        Parameters:
        path - The dot-separated path of the namespace for which command identifiers should be returned. If null identifiers of all commands registered with the infrastructure will be returned.
        Returns:
        Identifiers of the requested commands.
        Throws:
        NotFound - if a namespace corresponding to path doesn't exist.

      • fingerprint

        java.lang.String fingerprint()
        Returns the aggregate fingerprint of all the command metadata from all the metadata sources.

        The fingerprint provides clients an efficient way to check if the metadata for commands has been modified on the server.

        Synchronous method overload. Result of the invocation will be reported as a method return value.

        Returns:
        Fingerprint of all the command metadata present on the server.
